The paper deals with the concept of entropy and its application in a game involving questions and answers. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of Huffman codes, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the study of algorithms for optimal strategies, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
